support for console output only (stdout)
support for streaming built-in integral, float and string types (const char*, std::string)
independent logging contexts and independent log stream objects
severity levels: Debug, Info, Warn, Error
application id and context id printed as a prefix to each log message (4 characters only per id)
log level printed after context id and colour-coded (debug: green, info: blue, warn: yellow, error: red)
newline appended automatically to each log message
payload arguments separated by single whitespace
log message dumped with explicit flush or by destruction of stream object
log message not present when nothing streamed
stream object can be reused after explicit flush
filtering logging above severity threshold
logging reinitialization not possible (repeated calls ignored)
